.TH LO 1 "April 2026" "lo 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lo \- launch Node/Bun projects quickly for development
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lo
.RI [ project-name ]
.br
.B lo
.B --edit
.br
.B lo
.B --print-config
.br
.B lo
.B --help
.br
.B lo
.B --version
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lo
is a Bash CLI that speeds up daily frontend/backend development workflows.
It finds your project, detects package manager and script, installs dependencies
if needed, and launches your dev process in a detached terminal.
.PP
When no project name is provided, lo opens an interactive project menu:
.IP \[bu] 2
Uses
.B fzf
with a styled interface when available.
.IP \[bu] 2
Falls back to a numbered menu when fzf is not installed.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --edit
Configure the projects root directory and save it to config.
.TP
.B --print-config
Print the configured projects directory.
.TP
.B --help
Show usage help.
.TP
.B --version
Show current version.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Config file location:
.PP
.B ~/.config/lo/config
.PP
Expected format:
.PP
.EX
PROJECTS_DIR="/home/you/Projects"
.EE
.SH SCRIPT DETECTION
Inside the chosen project, lo checks
.B package.json
scripts in this order:
.IP "1." 3
.B dev
.IP "2." 3
.B start
.PP
If neither exists, lo exits with an error.
.SH PACKAGE MANAGER DETECTION
lo detects package manager by lockfile:
.IP \[bu] 2
.B pnpm-lock.yaml
->
.B pnpm
.IP \[bu] 2
.B bun.lock
or
.B bun.lockb
->
.B bun
.IP \[bu] 2
.B package-lock.json
->
.B npm
.PP
If no supported lockfile is found, lo exits with an error.
.SH TERMINAL LAUNCH
lo tries to launch in this order:
.IP "1." 3
.B ghostty
.IP "2." 3
.B kitty
.IP "3." 3
.B alacritty
.IP "4." 3
.B gnome-terminal
.PP
If none are available, lo runs in the current shell.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
Required:
.IP \[bu] 2
.B bash
.IP \[bu] 2
.B jq
.PP
Optional:
.IP \[bu] 2
.B fzf
(for interactive fuzzy menu)
.SH EXAMPLES
Start by exact project name:
.PP
.EX
lo api
.EE
.PP
Open interactive selector:
.PP
.EX
lo
.EE
.PP
Edit config:
.PP
.EX
lo --edit
.EE
.SH FILES
.B ~/.config/lo/config
.br
.B ~/.local/bin/lo
.br
.B ~/.local/share/man/man1/lo.1
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
General error, invalid config, missing dependency, or canceled selection.
